{"actual":"scan_secrets() never inspects '.env'-named files because of the suffix-allowlist filter, producing a silent false negative for exactly the case the policy is designed around.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus doctor's secret-pattern scanner silently skips dotfiles whose pathlib .suffix is empty, including files literally named '.env' — exactly the file class that .gitignore treats as sensitive — so credentials in such a file would not be flagged even if accidentally force-added.","classification":"SUSPECTED_DEFECT","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["Path('.env').suffix == '' in Python's pathlib (confirmed by direct evaluation in this environment).","scan_secrets() only scans a file if its suffix is in TEXT_SUFFIXES or its name is one of {'nexus', '.gitignore', '.gitattributes'}; '.env' matches neither.","In a full temporary copy of the repository (not the source repository), a '.env' file was created and force-added to git containing an AWS-style key line 'AKIAABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP' and an Anthropic-style key line 'ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-<placeholder>'. Calling scan_secrets() directly against that copy returned zero findings, even though both strings match SECRET_PATTERNS['AWS_ACCESS_KEY'] and SECRET_PATTERNS['ANTHROPIC_STYLE_KEY'].",".gitignore explicitly lists '.env' and '.env.*' under a '# Secrets and credentials' heading, confirming this file class is considered sensitive by policy."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/doctor.py:scan_secrets","system/nexus_lab/doctor.py:TEXT_SUFFIXES"],"expected":"The secret-pattern check exists specifically as a content-based backstop against committed credentials; a reasonable reader would expect it to cover the file names .gitignore itself calls out as credential-bearing.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/doctor.py",".gitignore"],"limitations":["This was demonstrated against a temporary copy of the repository, never against the source repository, and no real credential was used (synthetic placeholder values only, clearly not valid keys).","This is a gap in the content-scanning backstop specifically; the primary control (.gitignore preventing '.env' from being tracked at all) was not bypassed or tested here, only the secondary defense-in-depth control.","Other dotfile-style credential file names (e.g. '.npmrc', '.netrc') would have the same blind spot; not individually tested."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0011","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"Change the file-selection filter in scan_secrets() from an extension allowlist to a size-and-binary-detection based approach (attempt UTF-8 decode, skip on failure, as is already done) rather than gating on file extension at all, so no textual file class is silently exempted.","record_hash":"","reproduction":["cp -r <repo> /tmp/secrettest","cd /tmp/secrettest; printf 'AKIAABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP\\nANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX\\n' > .env","python3 -c \"import sys; sys.path.insert(0,'system'); from nexus_lab.doctor import scan_secrets; from pathlib import Path; print(scan_secrets(Path('.')))\"","observe an empty list"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"HIGH","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"Extend scan_secrets() to also scan files with empty suffix (dotfiles), or explicitly allowlist known credential-dotfile names ('.env', '.env.*', '.npmrc', '.netrc') for scanning regardless of suffix.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"The secret pattern anywhere in a >5MB file is never checked; run_doctor() reports secret_patterns: PASS with no indication that any file was excluded from scanning by size.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"APPARATUS","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"./nexus doctor's secret-pattern scanner unconditionally skips any file larger than 5MB, regardless of content, with no warning emitted that a large file was excluded from scanning.","classification":"SUSPECTED_DEFECT","confidence":"HIGH","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["In a temporary directory (not the source repository), a 6MB text file was created containing a leading line 'AKIAABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP' (matching SECRET_PATTERNS['AWS_ACCESS_KEY']) followed by 6MB of filler bytes. Calling scan_secrets() against that directory returned zero findings because `path.stat().st_size > 5 * 1024 * 1024` causes the file to be skipped entirely before any pattern matching occurs."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/doctor.py:scan_secrets"],"expected":"A secret near the start of an otherwise-large file should still be detected by a line-oriented regex scan; a 5MB cutoff with no diagnostic output means large files are an unannounced blind spot.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/doctor.py"],"limitations":["Tested only in a standalone temporary directory using the library function directly, not via the CLI against the source repository.","5MB is a reasonable performance guard for a fast local check; the finding is specifically that its exclusion is silent (not counted or logged anywhere in the doctor report), not that a size limit is inherently wrong."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0012","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["mkdir /tmp/bigfiletest","python3 -c \"open('/tmp/bigfiletest/big_secret.txt','wb').write(b'AKIAABCDEFGHIJKLMNOP\\n' + b'x'*(6*1024*1024))\"","python3 -c \"import sys; sys.path.insert(0,'system'); from nexus_lab.doctor import scan_secrets; from pathlib import Path; print(scan_secrets(Path('/tmp/bigfiletest')))\"","observe an empty list"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"MEDIUM","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"Have run_doctor() record a warning (e.g. 'SECRET_SCAN_SIZE_SKIPPED <path>') for every file excluded from scan_secrets() by the size guard, so the non-claim 'not exhaustive' has a concrete, inspectable list attached rather than being silent.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"Declared permissions and pinning practice both match common CI hardening guidance (least privilege, no floating-tag supply-chain trust, no persisted git credentials for subsequent steps).","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"OTHER","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"The GitHub Actions workflow (.github/workflows/nexus-audit.yml) declares least-privilege top-level permissions (contents: read), disables credential persistence on checkout (persist-credentials: false), and pins both actions/checkout and actions/setup-python to full 40-character commit SHAs rather than floating version tags.","classification":"OBSERVATION","confidence":"MEDIUM","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["File content read directly: 'permissions: contents: read' at workflow scope; 'uses: actions/checkout@08c6903cd8c0fde910a37f88322edcfb5dd907a8' with 'persist-credentials: false'; 'uses: actions/setup-python@ece7cb06caefa5fff74198d8649806c4678c61a1'."],"exact_location":[".github/workflows/nexus-audit.yml"],"expected":"CLAUDE_AUDIT_GUIDE.md requires verifying CI permissions and absence of committed credentials.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":[".github/workflows/nexus-audit.yml"],"limitations":["This environment has no network access, so the pinned commit SHAs for actions/checkout and actions/setup-python could not be verified against the real upstream github.com/actions repositories to confirm they resolve to the claimed, unmodified releases and not to some other or malicious commit. This specific supply-chain-authenticity property is UNABLE_TO_VERIFY here.","No live CI run was inspected (this audit had no GitHub Actions access); only the workflow source file was read."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0013","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"","record_hash":"","reproduction":["Read .github/workflows/nexus-audit.yml"],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"INFO","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"From an environment with GitHub access, confirm the pinned SHAs correspond to genuine actions/checkout and actions/setup-python releases and inspect at least one recent workflow run's permissions and logs.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
{"actual":"For newly created repositories, content is pushed as part of repo creation, and the PRIVATE check only runs afterward; if `--private` were ever ineffective (e.g. an organization policy override, an unexpected `gh` CLI behavior change, or a race with an external actor changing repo settings), the NexusError would fire only after data was already pushed.","audit_id":"AUD-R002-CLAUDE-BLIND","audit_layer":"OPERATOR_FRICTION","audit_phase":"BLIND","auditor":{"model_family":"Anthropic","model_name":"claude-sonnet-5","provider":"Anthropic","session_label":"second-account"},"claim":"In github_bootstrap(), when no origin remote exists yet, `gh repo create <name> --private --source=. --remote=origin --push` both creates the repository AND pushes local content in one call, before the subsequent `gh repo view` / require_private_visibility() check runs. The public-visibility guard is unit-tested only as an isolated pure function against synthetic JSON (test_github.py), not as an end-to-end guarantee that push cannot occur before visibility is confirmed.","classification":"SUSPECTED_DEFECT","confidence":"MEDIUM","created_at":"2026-07-12T23:30:00Z","evidence_refs":["Source inspection of github.py: when `origin` is empty, the code calls `_gh(root, 'repo', 'create', repo_name, '--private', '--source=.', '--remote=origin', '--push')` (which both creates and pushes) and only afterward calls `_gh(root, 'repo', 'view', ...)` followed by `require_private_visibility(full_name, visibility)`.","tests/test_github.py exercises only parse_visibility() and require_private_visibility() with hand-constructed JSON strings; it does not invoke github_bootstrap() itself or assert anything about push ordering."],"exact_location":["system/nexus_lab/github.py:github_bootstrap","tests/test_github.py"],"expected":"constitution/AUTHORITY.md-style protections against 'accidental creation or use of a public GitHub repository' (per docs/THREAT_MODEL.md in-scope threats) would ideally guarantee no content is pushed to a repository before its visibility is confirmed PRIVATE.","files_not_seen":[],"files_seen":["system/nexus_lab/github.py","tests/test_github.py"],"limitations":["This finding is based entirely on static source-code inspection. I did not execute github_bootstrap(): the GitHub CLI is not authenticated in this sandbox, and doing so would create real, irreversible external repository/push state outside the explicit scope of this read-only blind audit. This is UNABLE_TO_VERIFY by execution.","For the created=False branch (origin already exists), visibility is checked before the unconditional push later in the function, which does not have this specific ordering issue."],"observation_id":"AUDOBS-R002-CLAUDE-0014","previous_record_hash":"","recommended_future_change":"Split repository creation from the push: create with `gh repo create --private --source=. --remote=origin` (no --push), verify visibility via `gh repo view`, call require_private_visibility(), and only then perform the `git push`.","record_hash":"","reproduction":["Read system/nexus_lab/github.py lines documenting the create/push/view/verify sequence.","Read tests/test_github.py to confirm scope of existing coverage."],"schema":"nexus.audit-observation/v1","severity":"MEDIUM","status_authority":"NONE","suggested_next_test":"In a disposable, isolated GitHub account/sandbox, verify empirically whether `gh repo create --private --push` can ever result in transient or actual public exposure, and add an integration test (or a pre-push `gh repo view` check before the `--push`-combined create call) that fails closed.","target_archive_sha256":"33d3fb549d49e1ad02ac2b2880b5ab4336a6dc29a7142d3e33e4ec2694ad8603","target_commit":"7a8068fc6088b81cc9a7c94b49dc77e0abe592d8"}
